        options: ["Increase the oxytocin rate to expedite delivery","Reduce or discontinue the oxytocin infusion and reposition the patient","Administer terbutaline 0.5 mg IV push immediately","Continue monitoring without intervention since the tracing is not Category III"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Seven contractions in 10 minutes constitutes tachysystole. The priority intervention is to reduce or discontinue oxytocin and reposition the patient to improve uteroplacental perfusion. Terbutaline may be considered if tachysystole persists after stopping oxytocin but is given SQ (not IV) at 0.25 mg. Increasing oxytocin would worsen the situation."
